<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-01-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-01-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="374" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.00/1034.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-01-27"><hi rend="italic">January 27,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. McCreery says the Government of Honduras is informed that Gen.
                            Bonilla has taken Ceiba and that San Marcos de Colón, on the Nicaraguan
                            border, has been taken by his partisans.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>